Newly appointed state coordinator of Nigeria Midstream Downstream Petroleum Regulatory Authority (NMDPRA) Ahmed Emimaru has warned oil marketers to desist from selling above regulated price. The state NMDPRA boss who stated this at a meeting with the Independent Petroleum Marketers Association of Nigeria (IPMAN) and major marketers  to inform them on the new development in the oil and gas sector of the country,  also gave  a marching order to the workers to be productive and ensure quality service delivery to the people and nation. Emimaru told the marketers to desist from selling above the regulated price of products promising to strengthen monitoring and surveillance as frequently as possible henceforth. He urged IPMAN and major marketers to pass the message to their members and sensitize them adequately to ensure compliance. Emimaru also told the newly deployed workers to Minna office of the NMDPRA, that he will not spare anyone found wanting in the discharge of their duty as he will not allow anybody to undermine the standard of the organisation. He advised the workers to respect the organisational procedure in carrying out their responsibilities to enhance development. Responding, the chairman Independent Petroleum Marketers Association of Nigeria, Minna, Adamu Ahmed Erena called for harmonious working relationship between them, devoid of witch hunting. 